Subject: [PATCH] feat(landing): Ken Burns hero carousel, AWS-style
 header/footer, social icons
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

HERO
- New HeroCarousel component: 8 rotating Unsplash images matching the
  niche (mining, mining truck, agriculture, greenhouse, construction,
  geomembrane reservoir, transport, industrial plant)
- Ken Burns slow-zoom pan on the active slide, 6s rotation, 1.6s
  crossfade; respects prefers-reduced-motion
- Guaranteed navy base layer + dual dark overlays: hero is never blank
  and text contrast is always AA even if images are slow or fail
- Images load client-side (plain img) with per-image onError fallback

HEADER (AWS-style)
- Dark top utility bar above main nav: phone, WhatsApp, Contacto,
  and login/account link (hidden on mobile)

FOOTER (AWS-style)
- SÍGANOS social row + Volver arriba (back-to-top) link
- Privacy/Terms now real links

SOCIAL
- lib/social.ts: 9 platforms most used in South America (WhatsApp,
  Facebook, Instagram, TikTok, YouTube, LinkedIn, X, Telegram, Kwai)
- WhatsApp + Facebook point to real destinations; the other 7 are
  visible placeholders (href='#', disabled, 'próximamente' tooltip) so
  the layout is final and only the URL needs swapping in later
- Reusable SocialIcons component (dark/light variants)

LAYOUT
- scroll-smooth + id='top' anchor for back-to-top

Note: Unsplash CDN IDs could not be fetched from the build sandbox
(datacenter IP blocked). The fallback architecture guarantees a polished
hero regardless; verify the images on the deployed site and swap any
that don't fit — they're all in one array in HeroCarousel.tsx.

Verified: next build green (21 pages), tsc clean, runtime smoke test
confirms carousel + social + back-to-top render.
